4	1	Club Champs 2026	The draw for this year’s Championship will be sent out to members by 15h00 on Thursday, 14 March via SMS, email and on the website – NO changes to the draw will be accepted thereafter . \n\nThe tournament fee of R675pp will be charged automatically to your Club spending account upon confirmed entry or request an invoice. \n\nEach participant will then be required to register and check in for both rounds , on Saturday ( Round 1) & Sunday ( Round 2 ) in the Proshop . \n\nWe request all members to have a healthy credit on their club cards for ease of purchase over the weekend . \n\nAll participants are required to arrive a minimum of 40 minutes prior to their respective tee off time, register for each round and report to the starter on your stipulated tee box , a minimum of 12 minutes prior to tee off . \n\nPace of play is of the utmost importance, and we request all players to be very cognisant of the pace of play requirements to avoid being penalised. ( Max 2 hours per 9 holes, including grab and go). \n\nIt is the players responsibility to keep up pace of play at all times , to ensure an enjoyable championship experience for all participants. \n\nHandicaps were  frozen on Monday the 11th of March at 6pm . \n\nThe division ‘splits’ have been calculated (as per handicap index) and is sued with the draw. \n\nStandard local rules will be invalid and replaced with the Championship rules sheet below, which will also be provided at registration and on your respective tee box. \n\nAll players who wish to use a golf cart may do so - please pre book. (first come, first serve basis ) . \n\nA warmup 'bucket' will be included in your championship fee for the driving range. (one per day). \n\nWe plan to host the prize giving ceremony at 18h00 on Sunday evening, 17 March and encourage all members and their families to please attend, support and enjoy the celebration. \n\nThere will be kids activities, a live band, great food, drinks specials and much more. \n\nOutside caddies will be permitted for the Championship subject to wearing a Royal overall and paying the caddy service fee in the pro shop each day. \n\nIf you have any questions, please don't hesitate to contact us on 011 640 3021	2026-06-06	\N	\N	competition	open	\N	\N	active	1	2026-06-05 07:47:08.889796	2026-06-07	gross_stroke_play	[{"key": "A", "tees": "Yellow", "label": "A Division", "format": "stroke_play", "max_hcp": 9.9, "min_hcp": 0}, {"key": "B", "tees": "White", "label": "B Division", "format": "stroke_play", "max_hcp": 17.9, "min_hcp": 10}, {"key": "C", "tees": "Red", "label": "C Division", "format": "stableford", "max_hcp": 36, "min_hcp": 18}]	2026-06-05	2026-06-05	1	1	1	2	1	1	1	1		\N	\N	https://5b48a272-2c21-419d-9e86-c9f280702dda-00-2gx85khwemwzd.kirk.replit.dev/api/storage/objects/tournament-images/1/d74ecc52-3744-42b0-b373-71ac2bf757df..jpeg	1	18	[]	0	0	\N	0	\N	random	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	0	\N
